main event: An unidentified aerial object was reported over Fairfield, Illinois on October 9, 1963, observed by Mr. and Mrs. John Doe.
interesting points: The object was described as dark and elongated, approximately 20 to 25 feet long., It hovered at an altitude of 100 to 200 feet and had internal light illumination., The witnesses saw the object for about 2 to 3 minutes before it rapidly accelerated away., The weather conditions during the sighting were clear with no wind., Photographic evidence was obtained and is being analyzed by the USAF.
